<topic class="Popup" template="Default" status="Under Construction" modified="2024-05-05T19:29:20.096+01:00" lasteditedby="44785" version="2" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../../../helpproject.xsd">
  <title>Forces</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>Forces</keyword>
    <keyword>Kinetostatic-Forces</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="PopupTable" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small">Kinetostatic Forces</text> are those forces at <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Joints, 2D-Cams, Gears</text>, <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Pulleys</text>, and <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Belts</text> that result from the motions that are designed and imposed on <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Parts</text> and kinematic-chains with <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Mass</text> and <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Mass Moment of Inertia</text> properties.</para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">The <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Torque</text> or <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Force</text> that a motor must provide to move each kinematic-chain with the motions that you design for them is usually called the <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Application-Load</text>, particularly when sizing a motor or gearbox.</para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">We also use the terms: </para>
          <list id="0" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Popup Box" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small">Drive Torque</text>, which is the <text styleclass="VariableName-small">turning moment</text> a Rotary Motor, or Servomotor, must provide to a kinematic-chain.</li>
            <li styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small">Drive</text> (or <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Motive</text>) <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Force</text>, which is the <text styleclass="VariableName-small">linear force</text> a <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Linear Motor</text> must provide to a kinematic-chain.</li>
          </list>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
